[?2004l[?2004h> with open('/output/audit_findings.txt', 'w') as f:
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("AUDIT FINDINGS: FRAUD MODEL EVALUATION DRAFT REPORT\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("==================================================\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("Audited by: Senior AI Consultant / Lead Fraud Analyst\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("Date: May 27, 2026\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("Subject: Technical and Operational Audit of Draft Evaluation Report by Alex Chen (Junior Analyst)\n\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("This document contains detailed findings from our technical audit of the draft fraud model evaluation report. The audit revealed multiple critical errors, misleading claims, and major analytical gaps. Deploying the model under the draft's assumptions would have overwhelmed Fraud Operations and led to sub-optimal financial results.\n\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("Below are the 6 primary findings, including explanations of what is wrong, why it matters, and the corrected interpretations.\n\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("FINDING 1: Data Pipeline Failure (Out-of-Period Data and Duplicate Leakage)\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("* Claim in Draft:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  \"The XGBoost fraud detection model was evaluated against 5,650 held-out transactions.\"\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("* What is Wrong:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  The evaluation dataset export was not pre-processed or filtered. It contains 585 records from May (May 1 to May 11, 2026) which fall outside the designated scoring period of January 15 - April 30, 2026 specified in dataset_info.txt.\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  Crucially, 500 of these 585 records are exact duplicates (by TransactionID) of transactions already present within the correct scoring period. The analyst failed to perform basic deduplication and date filtering.\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("* Why it Matters:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  Including duplicate and out-of-period records inflates the evaluation dataset size by 11.5% and distorts all performance metrics. When properly cleaned, the true holdout dataset contains exactly 5,065 unique transactions and 0 duplicates.\n\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("FINDING 2: Inflated and Incorrect Performance Metrics\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("* Claim in Draft:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  \"Accuracy: 88.3%\", \"AUC-ROC: 0.9182\", \"Confusion Matrix (threshold = 0.5): True Positives: 194, False Positives: 604, False Negatives: 57, True Negatives: 4,795\"\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("* What is Wrong:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  These metrics were computed on the raw, uncleaned dataset of 5,650 rows (which included duplicate/leaked rows). On the corrected scoring period dataset (5,065 unique rows), the performance metrics are lower:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  - Correct AUC-ROC: 0.905062 (reported as 0.9182, an inflation of ~0.013)\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  - Correct Accuracy at 0.5: 88.0948% (reported as 88.30%)\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("  - Correct Confusion Matrix at 0.5:\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("    * True Positives (TP): 144 (reported as 194, an inflation of 50)\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("    * False Positives (FP): 554 (reported as 604, an inflation of 50)\n")
[?2004l[?2004h>     f.write("    * False Negatives (FN): 49 (reported as 57)\n")
